"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349898","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Department is not aware of a response to the Ankers Report by the Consumer Industry Council.</p><p> </p><p>The Department welcomed the Ankers report and is pleased to note that CICAIR has carried out some of the recommendations already and is making good progress with others.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-06-16T16:01:35.303Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349898/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349898/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-11","Building Inspectors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the implications for his Department's policy of the Consumer Industry Council's response to the recommendations made by the Ankers Report published in 2013.","false","Biography information for Mrs Maria Miller","Basingstoke","Mrs Maria Miller","2212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349899","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-17","<p /> <p>The sale price was dependent on market conditions, the prevailing share price and investors’ interest in buying the shares.</p><p> </p><p>Based on analysis from our independent financial adviser, the sale price achieved, 500p per share, represents value for money for the tax payer.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-17T09:32:30.2Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349899/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349899/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-11","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what estimate the Government made of the potential profit from the Government's holding in Royal Mail before the announcement of the sale of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","2251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349900","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-18","<p /> <p>No information is held on the proportion of households affected by the removal of the spare room subsidy that have received payments to mitigate in full the deductions from their housing benefit.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-18T13:01:20.787Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349900/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349900/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of households affected by the under-occupancy penalty have received payments to mitigate in full deductions from claims for (a) housing benefit and (b) local housing allowance in (i) England, (ii) Northern Ireland, (iii) Scotland and (iv) Wales.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349901","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p>We will publish a full Impact Assessment in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-16T11:53:59.937Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349901/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349901/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of reducing the benefits cap to £23,000 per annum on (a) young adults, (b) pregnant women, (c) couples with children, (d) veterans and (e) disabled people; and how many households in each of those groups will be affected by that reduction.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349902","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-17","<p /> <p>The Government takes into account likely impacts as part of its policy development process and will publish an impact assessment in due course.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-17T15:06:35.32Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349902/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349902/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the two year freeze on benefit levels on (a) young adults, (b) pregnant women, (c) couples with children, (d) formerly looked after children, (e) veterans and (f) disabled people; and what estimate he has made of the real terms effect on the levels of each type of benefit of that freeze.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349903","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p>Any changes to Housing Benefit policy will be subject to a full policy equality assessment to ascertain the impacts on protected groups and ensure compliance with the Public Sector Equality Duty.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-16T11:50:33.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349903/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349903/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will take steps to ensure planned changes to entitlements to housing benefit and local housing allowance do not adversely affect (a) young adults, (b) formerly looked after children, (c) pregnant women, (d) couples with children, (e) veterans and (f) disabled people.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349904","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p>Estimates of benefit take-up are not available at geographies below Great Britain. This is due to the size of the survey sample they are based on and methods used to generate robust national figures.</p><p> </p><p>Following a consultation at July 2012 on the future on the “Income Related Benefits: Estimates for Take-Up” National Statistics series, DWP are planning to publish Experimental Statistics on benefit take-up rates. Further details are available here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/announcements/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up-201213-experimental" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/announcements/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up-201213-experimental</a></p><p> </p><p>In February 2012 the Department for Work and Pensions published the report “Income Related Benefits: Estimates of Take-up in 2009-10”. The full report can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-related-benefits-estimates-of-take-up</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-16T11:49:59.91Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349904/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349904/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Scotland are not claiming what value of each benefit and pension entitlement; what proportion of each benefit and pension entitlement is unclaimed by claimants in Scotland; and if he will take steps to transfer the value of unclaimed benefits and pension entitlements to the Scottish Government.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349905","Scotland Office","false","2015-09-10","<p>The 14 Point Customer Charter was a commitment set out by RBS following an internal RBS review to improve customer service.</p><p>The Government welcomed the industry-wide Access to Banking protocol announced in March 2015. From the first of May this year, a bank must carry out a number of steps if it is closing a branch. The steps include establishing the impact of a branch closure before it takes place; finding suitable alternative provision; and putting satisfactory alternative measures in place before a branch is closed.</p><p>The UK government recognises the concerns for consumers and small businesses that branch closures continue to play in affected communities and wrote to the British Bankers’ Association to set out our expectations around effective compliance with the bank branch closure protocol.</p><p>The full text of the joint-letter by the Economic Secretary to the Treasury Harriett Baldwin MP and the Minister for Small Business, Industry and Enterprise Anna Soubry MP can found at the following:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/452900/Letter-from-Anna-Soubry-and-Harriet-Baldwin-to-British-Bankers-Association-branch-closures.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/452900/Letter-from-Anna-Soubry-and-Harriet-Baldwin-to-British-Bankers-Association-branch-closures.pdf</a></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-09-10T14:58:06.187Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349905/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349905/answer","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349905/answer/previousversion/5608","Biography information for David Mundell","2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-06-11","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, with reference to the statement by the Economic Secretary to the Treasury of 10 June 2015, if he will take steps to (a) ensure the Royal Bank of Scotland continues to meet the commitments in its 14 Point Customer Charter and (b) prevent the closure of Royal Bank of Scotland branches in Invergordon, Lochinver and Lybster.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2274"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349906","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 10 February 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=223115" target="_blank">UIN 223115</a>.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-16T11:42:50.813Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349906/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349906/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to ensure all people entitled to benefits and not claiming those benefits are identified and assisted in claiming those benefits.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","2273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349907","Home Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>We do not comment on police use of specific investigative techniques. Investigative activity involving interference with property or wireless telegraphy is regulated by the Police Act 1997 and the Intelligence Services Act 1994 which sets out the high level of authorisation required before the police or security and intelligence agencies can undertake such activity. Use of these powers is overseen by the Intelligence Services Commissioner and the Office of Surveillance Commissioners.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-16T15:24:38.027Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349907/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349907/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-11","Electronic Surveillance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether any UK police forces use International Mobile Subscriber Identity catchers.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","2118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349908","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>The guidance from the Cabinet Office released for the 2015 General Election states that the arrangements for the pre-election period apply “to all UK civil servants, and the board members and staff of non-departmental public bodies and other arm’s length bodies.” This applies to both NHS England and the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence as arm’s length bodies of the Department.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-16T15:31:59.043Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349908/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349908/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-11","NHS: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how purdah arrangements during election periods apply to staff working for NHS England and NICE.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","2139"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349909","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>In announcing the sale of the Government’s shareholding in Royal Bank of Scotland, the Chancellor is acting on independent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England and a report from Rothschild investment bank. The report by Rothschild, and the corresponding advice from the Governor, are both available online at www.gov.uk.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-18T11:52:48.907Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349909/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349909/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-11","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish the independent advice he received on the sale of the Government's stake in the Royal Bank of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","2105"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349910","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-17","<p>The Governments priorities are to support low and middle income households through increasing the income tax personal allowance to £12,500 and raising the higher rate threshold to £50,000. This will reduce taxes for over 30 million individuals.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-17T16:29:24.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349910/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349910/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-11","Income Tax: Tax Rates and Bands","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy not to reduce the top rate of tax.","false","Biography information for Gerald Jones","Merthyr Tydfil and Rhymney","Gerald Jones","2115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349911","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-18","<p>Treasury ministers consider a range of representations, and advice, as part of the policymaking process.<br><br>For example, Mr Angel Gurria, the Secretary-General of the OECD, said in February 2015 &quot;The United Kingdom is a textbook case of best practice on how good labour and product markets can support growth and job creation. So my main message to you today is &quot;well done and keep going with the plan!&quot;</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-18T11:32:59.66Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349911/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349911/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349911/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-11","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what advice he has taken from (a) economists independent of Government and (b) Treasury economists on whether public spending cuts will delay or promote economic growth.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","2140"
