"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349969","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-16","<p>We will publish a full Impact Assessment in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","2106 ; 2107 ; 2109","2015-06-16T13:33:52.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349969/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349969/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-11","Social Security Benefits: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of households with dependent children in (a) London, (b) Enfield and (c) Enfield North constituency that will be affected by a reduction of the benefit cap to £23,000.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","2108"
