"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350118","Department of Health","false","2015-06-23","<p>37 of the 153 National Health Service foundation trusts have a completed major (over £10 million capital cost) Private Finance Initiative scheme. Of these 37, 20 will end 2014-15 with a financial deficit.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-06-23T15:46:00.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350118/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350118/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350118/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-11","NHS Foundation Trusts: Private Finance Initiative","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many NHS foundation trusts have major Private Finance Initiative contracts; and how many of those hospitals are in debt.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350119","Cabinet Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>I refer the noble Baroness to the Prime Minister’s Written Ministerial Statement of 16 March. The government intends to publish the main findings of the Muslim Brotherhood Review, and the government’s Counter Extremism Strategy, in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-06-22T16:34:46.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350119/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350119/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350119/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-06-11","Muslim Brotherhood Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the report of the Muslim Brotherhood review will be published.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350120","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) supports greater dialogue between Sunni and Shia Muslims among all faith groups in the Middle East and North Africa region to build bridges, talk, listen and learn from each other. At the 27 March UN Security Council debate on the persecution of minorities in the Middle East, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), called for bold leadership from governments and communities in the region to continue working for tolerance and reconciliation. Where the British Government is best placed to act, and has the means to do so, we will. For example, in Syria a number of Government-funded projects have brought together religious leaders from all denominations (including Alawi, Christians, Kurds, Druze and Sunnis) to foster greater understanding between faiths and support reconciliation.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-06-22T11:26:15.413Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350120/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350120/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-11","Middle East","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what proposals they have for addressing interfaith conflict between Sunni and Shia Muslims in the Middle East.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350121","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-22","<p>Spending on projects to bring together interfaith communities is dispersed across Government and is a mainstream part of other Government activity. Disaggregating this spending would incur disproportional cost.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-06-22T11:26:43.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350121/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350121/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-11","Middle East","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much money has been invested in soft power in conflict zones in the Middle East in order to bring interfaith communities together.","false","Biography information for Baroness Manzoor",,"Baroness Manzoor","HL435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350122","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-23","<p>As at 1 April 2015, the average age of Army Reserve Officers was 26 years (untrained) and 44 years (trained), providing an overall average of 43 years.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-06-23T16:32:17.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350122/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350122/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-11","Army Reserve","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the average age of an Army Reserve Officer.","false","Biography information for Earl Attlee",,"Earl Attlee","HL436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350123","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-17","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) does not issue guidelines to prison governors. However, my officials work closely with their counterparts in the Ministry of Justice to address the issues facing veterans in the criminal justice system. We achieve effect through the Ex-Service Offenders Working Group (ESOWG) which includes the Ministry of Justice, the National Offender Management Service and Service charities.</p><p>The ESOWG aims to ensure that the ex-Service prison and probation offender populations, their families and resettlement services are fully informed of the support available from Defence Business Services, Veterans UK and the voluntary and charitable sectors. This support and assistance applies during imprisonment as well as pre- and post-discharge.</p><p>A key objective of the ESOWG is to ensure that the differing requirements of ex-Service prisoners are understood and communicated and that tailored support is available in those prison establishments with higher veteran populations.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2015-06-17T15:49:41.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350123/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/350123/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-11","Veterans: Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Ministry of Defence has issued to prison governors any guidelines on meeting the needs of prisoners who are armed forces veterans.","false","Biography information for Lord Ramsbotham",,"Lord Ramsbotham","HL437"
