"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349648","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-06-17","<p>The National Pollinator Strategy is a 10 year plan which sets out a framework for collective action to protect pollinators on farmland, towns, cities and the countryside, and to enhance the response to pests and disease risk. The Strategy also seeks to raise awareness of what pollinators need to thrive through a call to action message which sets out five simple actions that everyone can take to support pollinators (<a href="http://www.wildlifetrusts.org/Bees-needs" target="_blank">www.wildlifetrusts.org/Bees-needs</a>).</p><p>The Strategy is an important starting point and must be flexible, adapting to new data and understanding as this emerges. We will keep the Strategy under review, refreshing the aims by 2019 and identifying any necessary targets and additional policies to strengthen our response based on an improved understanding of the baselines, the impact of pressures and the role of pollinators. The review will also consider lessons learned from the initial policy actions and partnership working. We will coordinate the production of a one year progress report with key partners on implementation of the Strategy later this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-06-17T11:02:34.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349648/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349648/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-06-10","Pollinators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how frequently her Department plans to update the National Pollinator Strategy.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","1928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349649","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-06-17","<p>Statistics on revenue expenditure funding are published by local authority in the Revenue Outturn Summary, which are available at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-revenue-expenditure-and-financing</a></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-06-17T15:12:10.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349649/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349649/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-10","Local Government Finance: Enfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much the London Borough of Enfield local authority received in (a) central government funding and (b) government grants in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","1779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349650","Home Office","false","2015-06-17","<p>The public consultation on the draft Equipment Interference Code of Practice closed in April. The Government is considering the responses carefully and will respond in due course, taking into account all relevant recommendations made by David Anderson in his recent report on investigatory powers.</p><p>The Government is committed to ensuring that our security and intelligence legislation is fair, effective and proportionate and reflects our duty to protect the public and our interests overseas in a way that is consistent with our lawful rights, the rule of law and transparency. The legal regime governing equipment interference ensures that this activity is conducted compatibly with ECHR rights. The draft Equipment Interference Code of Practice sets out the procedures that must be followed before equipment interference can take place and provides guidance on the processing, retention, destruction and disclosure of any information obtained by means of the interference</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes","1862","2015-06-17T11:16:17.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349650/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349650/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-10","Electronic Surveillance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to publish the consultation response for the draft equipment interference code of practice.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","1781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349651","Home Office","false","2015-06-16","<p>No organisations or individuals have been granted exemptions from the provisions in the Computer Misuse Act 1990.</p><p>Section 10 of the Computer Misuse Act 1990 clarifies the interaction between the use of authorised powers and the Computer Misuse Act offences. It does not extend those powers, confer additional powers, or create new defences for the police, security and intelligence services.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-16T14:56:47.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349651/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349651/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-06-10","Computer Misuse Act 1990","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, which organisations and individuals have been granted exemptions from the provisions of the Computer Misuse Act 1990.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","1782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349652","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-19","<p /> <p>Data on the total value of exports are not available below the UK level. Data for the value of goods exports are published at regional level only by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) in Regional Trade Statistics. Data on the value of service exports by region are not available.</p><p> </p><p>Of the areas for which data have been requested only London has data available as this is reported as a region. The London region consists of the City of London and the 32 London Boroughs. The value of goods exports from the London region in the past five years is shown below.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has not made projections for the value of exports in the next five years.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="5"><p>International goods exports from the London region (£ billion)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>29.6</p></td><td><p>36.2</p></td><td><p>35.0</p></td><td><p>32.7</p></td><td><p>28.8</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p>Source: HMRC Regional Trade Statistics</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-19T13:49:14.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349652/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349652/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the value of international exports from (a) West Yorkshire, (b) North Yorkshire, (c) South Yorkshire, (d) East Yorkshire, (e) Greater Manchester, (f) Greater London and (g) Leeds was for each of the last five years; and whether his Department has made projections for that value in the next five years.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","1783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349653","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-19","<p>The Prompt Payment Code is a voluntary code for public, private and third sector organisations. Recent changes introduced a 30 day payment terms as a target which all signatories should work towards, and a maximum 60 day term. Whilst all signatories are actively encouraged to start complying with this early, it will come into force next year.</p><p> </p><p>The Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015 provides the power to introduce a reporting requirement for all large companies to report on their payment practices and performance. This requirement will be used to monitor the payment performance of large company signatories to the Code.</p><p> </p><p>A company which is registered in the UK will be subject to the new reporting requirements, regardless of where its payment department is located.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-19T09:23:13.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349653/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349653/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Companies: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to ensure that companies do not circumvent the 30-day standard for paying suppliers by relocating their payment departments to other countries.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","1784"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349654","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-06-15","<p>A comprehensive nuclear deal with Iran that addresses our proliferation concerns will need to be fully verifiable by the International Atomic Energy Agency. This must include robust monitoring of Iran’s nuclear activities, and Iran’s implementation of it's Additional Protocol, in order to reassure the international community that Iran’s nuclear programme is exclusively peaceful.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-06-15T15:27:42.117Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349654/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349654/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-06-10","Iran: Nuclear Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the proposal by Iran under a nuclear deal for a 24-day notification period for access to nuclear facilities in that country by International Atomic Energy Agency inspectors.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","1789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349655","Department of Health","false","2015-06-17","<p>The Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC) is a self-financing, independent regulator that is accountable to Parliament through the Professional Standards Authority whose role is to assess the HCPC’s performance, conduct audits, scrutinise their decisions and report to Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In determining the level of fee increase the HCPC undertook a public consultation and considered the responses before setting the fee.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is for the council of the HCPC to determine what evaluation it commissions on its recent increase in mandatory registration fees.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-17T10:35:21.293Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349655/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349655/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Health and Care Professions Council: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to encourage the Health and Care Professions Council to evaluate the effect of its recent increase in mandatory registration fees.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","1792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349656","Department of Health","false","2015-06-18","<p>The number of mental health beds provided in the West Midlands is not centrally collected.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-18T09:46:44.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349656/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349656/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Mental Health Services: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many mental health beds are provided in (a) Birmingham and (b) the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","1806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349657","Department of Health","false","2015-06-18","<p>The Department does not have arrangements for bed management as this is the responsibility of local commissioners and providers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, the Government has made it clear that beds must always be available for those that need them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Hospital, step-down and community services should be commissioned at a level that allows for beds to be readily and locally available in response to a person in urgent need, as required by statute.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>As to arrangements in place between mental health trusts when no beds are available, this is a matter for local commissioners and providers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This is underpinned by the Government’s legislation on party esteem for the first time, and significant investment in mental health services.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","1809","2015-06-18T11:19:16.383Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349657/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349657/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Mental Health Services: Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what arrangements his Department has in place to assist mental health trusts when no beds are available for the provision of mental health care.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","1807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349658","Department of Health","false","2015-06-18","<p>NHS England holds a NHS standard contract with Cygnet Healthcare. The contract is managed by the South of England Team for all provision across England. The contract is managed in accordance with its terms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Any local contracts with Cygnet Healthcare are likely to be subcontracted by mental health provider trusts. Details of these are not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-18T09:53:45.577Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349658/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349658/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","NHS: Cygnet Health Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what contractual arrangements exist between NHS mental health services and Cygnet Health Care.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","1808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349659","Department of Health","false","2015-06-18","<p>The Department does not have arrangements for bed management as this is the responsibility of local commissioners and providers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, the Government has made it clear that beds must always be available for those that need them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Hospital, step-down and community services should be commissioned at a level that allows for beds to be readily and locally available in response to a person in urgent need, as required by statute.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>As to arrangements in place between mental health trusts when no beds are available, this is a matter for local commissioners and providers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This is underpinned by the Government’s legislation on party esteem for the first time, and significant investment in mental health services.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","1807","2015-06-18T11:19:16.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349659/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349659/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Mental Health Services: Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what arrangements mental health and NHS trusts have in place to provide mental health care when no mental health care beds are available.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","1809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349660","Department of Health","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Department has made no such assessment.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-06-16T14:57:33.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349660/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349660/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-10","Birmingham and Solihull Mental Health NHS Foundation Trust: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of Birmingham and Solihull Mental Health Trust in meeting demand for treating patients referred for mental health conditions.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","1810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349661","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>The UK Government is committed to making the Digital Single Market a reality. Any copyright reform should aim to deepen the Digital Single Market, promoting wider legal access to copyright material and not standing in the way of technological innovation, while continuing to protect and reward creativity. At the meeting of the Education, Youth, Culture and Sport Council, the United Kingdom highlighted the importance of getting this balance right.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-30T08:58:54.867Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349661/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349661/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-10","Digital Technology: EU Internal Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Written Statement of 8 June 2015, HCWS17, on the Education, Youth, Culture and Sport Council, what specific concerns the UK representative raised about the implications of the Digital Single Market for copyright and for funding content.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","1817"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349662","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-15","<p>The findings of the stocktake will be published in due course</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-06-15T10:28:47.847Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349662/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349662/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-10","Youth Offending Teams","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 8 June 2015 to Question 1068, if he will publish the results of his Department's stock-take of youth offending teams.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","1819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349663","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-06-16","<p>Onshore wind has made a valuable contribution to the UK energy mix in recent years and we are confident that it will make its expected contribution to the UK’s carbon reduction and renewables targets. However, the Government is committed to ending new subsidies for onshore wind as soon as possible; in doing so, we will consider carefully the impact on investments affected by the measures that we bring forward.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-06-16T13:13:15.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349663/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349663/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-10","Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of the investment value of projects which are in the onshore wind development pipeline.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","1834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349664","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-16","<p>As was the case for the recent sale, any future sales would require us to work with advisers to consider our sale options and assess which one best meets the stated sale objectives.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, at any time, Royal Mail shares are directly available to retail investors as they are freely traded on the stock market.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-16T10:20:21.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349664/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349664/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what provision he plans to make in the sale of the remaining public stake of Royal Mail for shares to be made available to retail investors directly; and what evidence he has consulted or research he has commissioned in relation to that option.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","1836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349665","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-16","<p>No decision has been made on the payment of this discretionary fee.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The stabilisation period has been completed.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-16T16:07:39.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349665/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349665/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Answer of 1 September 2014 (HC Deb C666W), by what date he plans to make a decision on the payment of the discretionary fee and the length of the stabilisation period following the privatisation of Royal Mail.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","1837"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349666","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-16","<p>The accelerated book build process, used in the recent sale, did not involve the concept of priority investors in the same way as a typical Initial Public Offering process would. There was not a need for early engagement by potential investors.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>All leading long term investors were invited to bid for shares.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-16T10:18:18.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349666/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349666/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department plans to seek and identify priority investors in respect of its sale of the remaining public stake in Royal Mail; and whether he intends to prioritise long-term investors in that sale.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","1838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349667","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Government has appointed Rothschild to provide independent financial advice and Freshfields to provide external legal advice. The syndicate of banks were Bank of America Merrill Lynch, Goldman Sachs and JP Morgan.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-16T10:19:19.923Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349667/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349667/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-10","Royal Mail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, which banks or syndicate of banks are (a) advising the Government and (b) overseeing the sale of the remaining public stake in Royal Mail; and whether any other banks, institutions or firms have involvement in that process.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","1839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349668","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government will consider signing the Council of Europe Convention on the Manipulation of Sports Competitions once discussions on the European Commission's proposals for the EU to become a signatory have concluded.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-06-29T14:43:30.093Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349668/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349668/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-10","Council of Europe Convention on the Manipulation of Sports Competitions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether it is the Government's policy that the UK will sign the Council of Europe Convention on the Manipulation of Sports Competitions.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","2001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349669","Prime Minister","false","2015-06-16","<p>The Home Affairs Cabinet Committee covers a wide range of domestic policy including the arts and the creative industries. The Government has established the Creative Industries Council, jointly co-chaired by the Secretaries of State for Culture, Media and Sport and Business, Innovation and Skills, with an industry co-chair, Nicola Mendelsohn (Vice-President, Facebook).</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-06-16T16:01:22.21Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349669/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/349669/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-06-10","Cabinet Committees: Arts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will establish a Cabinet Committee on the Arts and Creative Industries.","false","Biography information for Chris Bryant","Rhondda","Chris Bryant","2002"
